                <div class="block">
                    <span class="block_heading">NATURE OF ENDORSEMENT</span>
                    <p class="block_body">
                        1. This Endorsement extends to insure the Policyholder against losses arising from
                        <b>insurable contract</b> and resulted directly from any of the events specified in Clause 4 of this
                        Endorsement which occurs after the
                        <b>insurable contract</b>
                        is made but before
                        <b>shipment</b>. This Endorsement applies only to the
                        <b>insurable contract</b>s made between the Policyholder and the overseas buyer(s) specified in the
                        Schedule to this Endorsement.
                    </p>
                    <p class="block_body">
                        2. The terms and conditions of the Policy apply equally to this Endorsement except to the extent that they are varied, deleted
                        or added. For the purpose of this Endorsement, where the context admits:
                        <p class="sub_1">
                            (a)
                            <b>“Claim payment”</b> means the payment to be made by HKECIC to the Policyholder as specified in
                            Clause 18 of this Endorsement.
                        </p>
                        <p class="sub_1">
                            (b)
                            <b>“Contract price”</b> means the sum payable for goods to be shipped under the
                            <b>insurable contract</b>, including any insurance, freight or other charges payable by the Policyholder
                            on behalf of the buyer and any interest charges payable by the buyer for credit facilities provided
                            by the Policyholder.
                        </p>
                        <p class="sub_1">
                            (c)
                            <b>“Costs of work in progress”</b> means the costs incurred by the Policyholder in procuring the
                            goods required under the insurable contract before
                            <b>shipment</b>, which include the following where applicable:
                        </p>
                        <p class="sub_2">
                            (i) the amount of costs of direct wages and materials necessarily and solely incurred by the Policyholder for the production
                            of the goods required under the
                            <b>insurable contract</b>; and/or
                        </p>
                        <p class="sub_2">
                            (ii) in relation to goods required under the
                            <b>insurable contract</b> being acquired by the Policyholder by way of purchase from a third party,
                            the amount the Policyholder is liable to pay to the third party for the goods required under
                            the
                            <b>insurable contract</b>;
                        </p>
                        <p class="sub_1">
                            up to but not exceeding the
                            <b>contract price</b> and must be evidenced by documentary proof to the reasonable satisfaction
                            of HKECIC.
                        </p>
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div style="page-break-after:always;" />
            <div style="page-break-before:always;" />
            <div class="page_3">

                <div class="block">
                    <span class="block_heading"></span>
                    <p class="block_body">
                        <p class="sub_1">
                            <b>“Date of loss”</b> means the date on which all the raw materials, work-in-progress and/or finished
                            goods in relation to the insurable contract concerned not accepted by the buyer or in the possession
                            or control of the Policyholder, if any, have been resold or disposed of by the Policyholder,
                            or the date set out in the following (i) to (iii), whichever is the later:
                        </p>
                        <p class="sub_2">
                            (i) the date on which the first event of
                            <b>insolvency</b> occurs where the
                            <b>event of loss</b> is specified in Clause 4(a) of this Endorsement;
                        </p>
                        <p class="sub_2">
                            (ii) four months after the date of payment of local currency deposit or four months after the
                            <b>due date</b>, whichever is the later where the
                            <b>event of loss</b> is specified in Clause 4(c) of this Endorsement. If the buyer is prohibited
                            from making the deposit, four months after the
                            <b>due date</b>; or
                        </p>
                        <p class="sub_2">
                            (iii) in the
                            <b>events of loss</b> specified in Clauses 4(d), 4(e), 4(f) and 4(g) of this Endorsement, four months
                            after the occurrence of the event.
                        </p>
                        <p class="sub_2">
                            In case where the
                            <b>event of loss</b> is specified in Clause 4(b) of this Endorsement, the date on which the raw
                            materials, work-in-progress and/or finished goods in relation to the
                            <b>insurable contract</b> concerned not accepted by the buyer or in the possession or control of
                            the Policyholder, if any, have been resold or disposed of by the Policyholder.
                        </p>
                        <p class="sub_1">
                            (e)
                            <b>“Pre-shipment limit”</b> means the maximum
                            <b>amount of loss</b> HKECIC may be liable to the Policyholder in respect of a buyer in relation
                            to loss arising before
                            <b>shipment</b>.
                        </p>
                    </p>
                    <p class="block_body">
                        3. For the purpose of this Endorsement, all references to the following terms in the Policy shall be adopted as follows:
                        <p class="sub_1">
                            (a) all references to
                            <b>“gross invoice value”</b> in the Policy shall be deemed as references to the
                            <b>contract price</b>, save as to Clause 71 of the Policy and except otherwise provided for in this
                            Endorsement;
                        </p>
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div style="page-break-after:always;" />
            <div style="page-break-before:always;" />
            <div class="page_4">

                <div class="block">
                    <span class="block_heading"></span>
                    <p class="block_body">
                        <p class="sub_1">
                            (b) all references to
                            <b>“credit limit”</b> in the Policy shall be deemed as references to the
                            <b>pre-shipment limit</b>, save as to Clause 39 of the Policy and except otherwise provided for
                            in this Endorsement;
                        </p>
                        <p class="sub_1">
                            (c) all references to
                            <b>“shipment”</b> shall be deemed as references to the
                            <b>insurable contract</b>, save as to Clauses 2, 4, 17.5, 18.3, 39, 40, 71 and 77 of the Policy
                            and except otherwise provided for in this Endorsement.
                        </p>
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="block">
                    <span class="block_heading">THE COVER</span>
                    <p class="block_body">
                        4. The
                        <b>events of loss</b> covered under this Endorsement are:
                        <p class="sub_1">
                            (a) the
                            <b>insolvency</b> of the buyer;
                        </p>
                        <p class="sub_1">
                            (b) the repudiation of the
                            <b>insurable contract</b> by the buyer before
                            <b>shipment</b>;
                        </p>
                        <p class="sub_1">
                            (c) the operation of an
                            <b>applicable law or regulation</b> of the buyer’s
                            <b>country</b> which, beyond the control of both the Policyholder and the buyer, prevents or restricts
                            the transfer of payment to Hong Kong but only if the buyer has paid the equivalent amount payable
                            in local currency into a bank account with an irrevocable instruction for transfer to the Policyholder,
                            to the extent the law allows;
                        </p>
                        <p class="sub_1">
                            (d) the imposition of an
                            <b>applicable law or regulation</b> by the buyer's
                            <b>country</b> which, beyond the control of both the Policyholder and the buyer, prevents the import
                            of the goods into the buyer's
                            <b>country</b>;
                        </p>
                        <p class="sub_1">
                            (e) the cancellation of a previously issued authority to import goods by the buyer's
                            <b>country</b> which is beyond the control of both the Policyholder and the buyer and without any
                            fault of either of them;
                        </p>
                        <p class="sub_1">
                            (f) a general moratorium decreed by the buyer’s
                            <b>country</b> or by a third
                            <b>country</b> through which the payment must be effected; and
                        </p>
                        <p class="sub_1">
                            (g) the occurrence of war, revolution or riot, or any natural disaster in the buyer's
                            <b>country</b> which in whole or in part prevents performance of the
                            <b>insurable contract</b>.
                        </p>
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div style="page-break-after:always;" />
            <div style="page-break-before:always;" />
            <div class="page_5">

                <div class="block">
                    <span class="block_heading"></span>
                    <p class="block_body">
                        <p class="sub_1">
                            For the sake of clarity, the
                            <b>events of loss</b> covered under the Policy shall be varied and replaced by Clause 4 of this
                            Endorsement.
                        </p>
                        <p class="sub_2"></p>
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="block">
                    <span class="block_heading">ADDITIONAL CONDITIONS</span>
                    <p class="block_body">
                        The additional conditions to this Endorsement are:
                        <p class="sub_1">
                            5. The Policyholder must
                            <b>export</b> the goods within a period of six months from the date of
                            <b>insurable contract</b> unless otherwise agreed by HKECIC in writing.
                        </p>
                        <p class="sub_1">
                            6. If the
                            <b>insurable contract</b> is made on terms different from Clause 3 of the Policy, the Policyholder
                            must inform HKECIC in writing within 21 days after the
                            <b>insurable contract</b> is made, and HKECIC shall advise the Policyholder whether such
                            <b>insurable contract</b> shall be covered or excluded.
                        </p>
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="block">
                    <span class="block_heading">PRE-SHIPMENT LIMIT</span>
                    <p class="block_body">
                        <p class="sub_1">
                            7. (a) The Policyholder must have a
                            <b>pre-shipment limit</b> approved by HKECIC for each buyer and the
                            <b>pre-shipment limit</b> may contain additional conditions of cover forming part of the Policy.
                        </p>
                        <p class="sub_1">
                            (b) HKECIC may cancel or vary any provision of the Policy in writing including the
                            <b>pre-shipment limit</b> on any buyer or the cover on any
                            <b>country</b>. Any such cancellation or variation shall only apply to
                            <b>insurable contract</b>s made on or after the effective date specified in HKECIC’s notice.
                        </p>
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="block">
                    <span class="block_heading">
                        <b>amount of loss</b>
                    </span>
                    <p class="block_body">
                        8. For the purpose of this Endorsement,
                        <b>“Amount of loss”</b> means:
                        <p class="sub_1">
                            (a) in relation to loss arising before
                            <b>shipment</b>, the
                            <b>contract price</b> multiplied by a figure which is equal to the proportion of costs of work in
                            progress incurred by the Policyholder at the date of
                            <b>claim payment</b> bears to the amount of total costs of direct wages and materials necessarily
                            and solely required for the performance of the
                            <b>insurable contract</b> by the Policyholder, less the following where applicable:
                        </p>
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="page_6">

                <div class="block">
                    <span class="block_heading"></span>
                    <p class="block_body">
                        <p class="sub_2">
                            (i) any
                            <b>contract price</b> including any deposit payable under the
                            <b>insurable contract</b> which has been paid;
                        </p>
                        <p class="sub_2">
                            (ii) any expense or interest saved by the Policyholder due to non-fulfilment of the
                            <b>insurable contract</b>;
                        </p>
                        <p class="sub_2">
                            (iii) any counter-claim or set-off which can be used by the buyer to reduce the
                            <b>contract price</b>;
                        </p>
                        <p class="sub_2">
                            (iv) any reduction of payment mutually agreed between the Policyholder and the buyer;
                        </p>
                        <p class="sub_2">
                            (v) any sum the Policyholder has received from the realisation of any security, and / or the amount or value mutually agreed
                            between the Policyholder and HKECIC in respect of any enforceable security held by the Policyholder
                            which can be used by the Policyholder;

                        </p>
                        <p class="sub_2">
                            (vi) any amount mutually agreed between the Policyholder and HKECIC; and/or
                        </p>
                        <p class="sub_2">
                            (vii) any sum the Policyholder has received from any source including the resale of any raw materials, work-in-progress and
                            finished goods.

                        </p>
                        <p class="sub_1">
                            (b) in relation to loss arising before
                            <b>shipment</b> and where the Policyholder does not produce or manufacture the goods required under
                            the
                            <b>insurable contract</b> and the goods are acquired by the Policyholder by way of purchase from
                            a third party, the
                            <b>contract price</b> multiplied by a figure which is equal to the proportion of costs of work in
                            progress the Policyholder is liable to pay at the date of
                            <b>claim payment</b> bears to the price of the goods agreed to be paid by the Policyholder to the
                            third party had the contract between the Policyholder and the third party been performed, less
                            the following where applicable:
                        </p>

                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div style="page-break-after:always;" />
            <div style="page-break-before:always;" />
            <div class="page_7">

                <div class="block">
                    <span class="block_heading"></span>
                    <p class="block_body">
                        <!-- <p class="sub_1"></p> -->
                        <p class="sub_2">
                            (i) any
                            <b>contract price</b> including any deposit payable under the
                            <b>insurable contract</b> which has been paid;
                        </p>
                        <p class="sub_2">
                            (ii) any expense or interest saved by the Policyholder due to non-fulfilment of the
                            <b>insurable contract</b>;
                        </p>
                        <p class="sub_2">
                            (iii) any counter-claim or set-off which can be used by the buyer to reduce the
                            <b>contract price</b>;

                        </p>
                        <p class="sub_2">
                            (iv) any reduction of payment mutually agreed between the Policyholder and the buyer;

                        </p>
                        <p class="sub_2">
                            (v) any sum the Policyholder has received from the realisation of any security, and / or the amount or value mutually agreed
                            between the Policyholder and HKECIC in respect of any enforceable security held by the Policyholder
                            which can be used by the Policyholder;
                        </p>
                        <p class="sub_2">
                            (vi) any amount mutually agreed between the Policyholder and HKECIC; and/or
                        </p>
                        <p class="sub_2">
                            (vii) any sum the Policyholder has received from any source including the resale of any raw materials, work-in-progress and
                            finished goods.
                        </p>
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="block">
                    <span class="block_heading">DECLARATIONS AND PREMIUMS</span>
                    <p class="block_body">
                        <p class="sub_1">
                            9. The Policy requires the Policyholder to declare all
                            <b>insurable contract</b>s concluded with all buyers specified in the Schedule to this Endorsement.
                            The Policyholder must declare to HKECIC in the form specified by HKECIC (or in such other form
                            acceptable to HKECIC):
                        </p>
                        <p class="sub_2" style="background-color:yellow;">
                            9.1 the
                            <b>contract price</b> of the goods contracted within 21 days from the date of the
                            <b>insurable contract</b>; or
                        </p>
                        <p class="sub_2" style="background-color:yellow;">
                            9.2 for each of the buyers within 15 days of the following month the aggregate amount of the
                            <b>contract price</b> of the goods contracted in the
                        </p>
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div style="page-break-after:always;" />
            <div style="page-break-before:always;" />
            <div class="page_8">

                <div class="block">
                    <span class="block_heading"></span>
                    <p class="block_body">
                        <span class="sub_1" style="background-color:yellow">
                            preceding month.
                        </span>
                    </p>
                    <span class="block_body" style="background-color:yellow;color:red;">
                        (to be confirmed)
                    </span>
                </div>
                <div class="block">
                    <span class="block_heading"></span>
                    <p class="block_body">
                        10. The Policyholder must pay premium within 14 days from the date of invoice issued by HKECIC showing the premium payable
                        for
                        <b>insurable contract</b>s declared. Premium is calculated on the
                        <b>contract price</b> of goods at the appropriate rates specified in the Schedule to this Endorsement
                        which may be amended from time to time by HKECIC.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="block">
                    <span class="block_heading"></span>
                    11. HKECIC has the right to change any premium rate applicable to
                    <b>insurable contract</b>s from time to time by giving the Policyholder prior written notice. In the case
                    where HKECIC increases the premium rate, the Policyholder may within 14 days from the date of such notice
                    inform HKECIC in writing to exclude from cover all (but not part) of the insurable contracts made on
                    or after the effective date of the increase of the premium rate.
                </div>
                <div class="block">
                    <span class="block_heading">NOTIFICATION OF LIKELY LOSS</span>
                    <p class="block_body">
                        12. When the Policyholder becomes aware of the occurrence of any
                        <b>event of loss</b>, or any event likely to cause loss, or that the buyer is or appears to be unable
                        to pay debts incurred in the ordinary course of business as and when they fall due, or the buyer
                        is or appears to be unable to pay the deposit or requests to lower the deposit requirement after
                        <b>insurable contract</b> has been made, the Policyholder must promptly and in any event within five
                        <b>business days</b> of such event inform HKECIC.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="block">
                    <span class="block_heading">ACTIONS AND EXPENSES FOR PREVENTING OR MINIMISING LOSSES</span>
                    <p class="block_body">
                        13. The Policyholder must act as if uninsured and promptly take all reasonable and practicable measures and all practicable
                        actions required by HKECIC to prevent or minimise losses at all times. Such measures or actions include,
                        but are not limited to the appointment of debt collectors, the institution of legal proceedings against
                        the buyer or any guarantor of the buyer and the exercise of any rights in respect of any security
                        held by the Policyholder, and the resale or disposal of the raw materials purchased and the work-in-progress
                        carried out for the purpose of the
                        <b>insurable contract</b>s and the goods sold under the
                        <b>insurable contract</b>s. In case of
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div style="page-break-after:always;" />
            <div style="page-break-before:always;" />
            <div class="page_9">

                <div class="block">
                    <span class="block_heading"></span>
                    <p class="block_body">
                        resale or disposal as mentioned, the Policyholder must obtain HKECIC’s prior written approval before action.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div style="margin-top:20%;"></div>
                <div class="block">
                    <span class="block_heading"></span>
                    <p class="block_body">
                        14. On the condition that the Policyholder has obtained HKECIC’s prior written approval for incurring any legal costs or
                        other charges for the purpose of preventing or minimising losses, HKECIC shall reimburse the Policyholder
                        for any such unrecovered legal costs or other charges as follows:
                        <table width="70%" border="1" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" style="margin:5%;">
                            <tr>
                                <td style="width:20%;text-align:center;">
                                    Unrecovered legal costs and other charges
                                </td>
                                <td style="width:20%;text-align:center;">
                                    x
                                </td>
                                <td style="width:20%;text-align:center;">
                                    The lower of the total amount of
                                    <b>contract price</b> and/or
                                    <b>
                                        <b>gross invoice value</b>
                                    </b> or
                                    <b>pre-shipment limit</b> and/or credit limit
                                    <br/> ______________________________
                                    <br/> Total indebtedness owed by the buyer to the Policyholders
                                </td>
                                <td style="width:20%;text-align:center;">
                                    x
                                </td>
                                <td style="width:20%;text-align:center;">
                                    <b>
                                        <b>Percentage of indemnity</b>
                                    </b>
                                </td>
                            </tr>
                        </table>
                        The appointment of any loss adjuster and the sharing of its related costs, expenses or fees incurred are specified in Clause
                        15 of this Endorsement.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="block">
                    <span class="block_heading"></span>
                    15. HKECIC shall reimburse the Policyholder half of any costs, expenses, fees and charges incurred for the purpose of appointing
                    any loss adjuster or person mutually agreed to be appointed to determine the fact and/or the extent of
                    the loss and/or the steps to be taken to mitigate such loss.
                </div>
                <div class="block">
                    <span class="block_heading"></span>
                    <p class="block_body">
                        16. HKECIC shall make the reimbursement specified in Clause 14 and/or Clause 15 of this Endorsement at the time of claim
                        payment. If no
                        <b>claim payment</b> becomes payable, HKECIC shall make the reimbursement after the unpaid contract
                        price and/or
                        <b>
                            <b>gross invoice value</b>
                        </b> is settled.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="block">
                    <span class="block_heading">EXCLUSIONS</span>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div style="page-break-after:always;" />
            <div style="page-break-before:always;" />
            <div class="page_10">

                <div class="block">
                    <span class="block_heading"></span>
                    <p class="block_body">
                        17. For the purpose of this Endorsement, Clauses 17.1, 17.2 and 17.5 of the Policy shall be deleted in their entirety and
                        replaced by the following:
                        <p class="sub_1">
                            “17.1 the Policyholder has not held a valid
                            <b>pre-shipment limit</b> for the buyer concerned;
                        </p>
                        <p class="sub_1">
                            17.2 the Policyholder has failed to declare any
                            <b>insurable contract</b>s in relation to this Endorsement in accordance with Clause 9 of this Endorsement
                            or make declarations as required under any other policies it has entered with HKECIC;”
                        </p>
                        The remainder of Clause 17 shall remain unchanged.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="block">
                    <span class="block_heading">CALCULATION OF LOSS AND CLAIM PAYMENT</span>
                    <p class="block_body">
                        18. In relation to loss arising before
                        <b>shipment</b>, HKECIC shall pay to the Policyholder the LESSER of:
                        <p class="sub_1">
                            18.1 the
                            <b>amount of loss</b> multiplied by the
                            <b>Percentage of indemnity</b>; or
                        </p>
                        <p class="sub_1">
                            18.2 the
                            <b>pre-shipment limit</b> multiplied by the
                            <b>Percentage of indemnity</b>.
                        </p>
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="block">
                    <span class="block_heading">ALLOCATION OF MONEY RECEIVED</span>
                    <p class="block_body">
                        19. Unless otherwise agreed by HKECIC, any payment, whether or not relating to the
                        <b>insurable contract</b>s, received after cancellation of the
                        <b>pre-shipment limit</b> and/or the credit limit by HKECIC on any buyer shall be deemed to reduce the
                        costs of work in progress which have been incurred and/or the outstanding amount which has fallen
                        due first even though the buyer may have indicated that the payment was in settlement of an outstanding
                        amount falling due at some later date or
                        <b>costs of work in progress</b>incurred or even such payment was not in respect of the insurable contracts.
                    </p>
                    <p class="block_body">
                        20. Unless otherwise agreed by HKECIC in writing, the date and amount of
                        <b>costs of work in progress</b>incurred specified in Clause 8 and Clause 19 of this Endorsement must
                        be calculated in accordance with generally accepted accounting principles in Hong Kong.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="block">
                    <span class="block_heading">CONVERSION OF FOREIGN CURRENCIES</span>
                </div>
            </div>
